@page "/Projects/Website"

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1>Blazor Portfolio Website</h1>
    <p class="lead">A personal portfolio website created using C#, Blazor to showcase skills, projects, and experience.</p>

    <!-- Project Overview -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Project Overview</h2>
        <p>This project is a personal portfolio website built entirely with Blazor, Microsoft’s modern web framework for building single-page applications (SPAs) in C#. The goal of this website is to provide a visually engaging and interactive platform where I can present my skills, highlight key projects, and offer potential employers or collaborators a way to connect with me.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Features -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>About Me Section:</strong> Provides a brief personal introduction, career goals, and contact links to give visitors an overview of who I am.</li>
            <li><strong>Projects Showcase:</strong> A gallery of project cards, each representing a different project. Users can click on each card to view a more detailed description, technology stack, and links to GitHub repositories or live demos.</li>
            <li><strong>Skills Section:</strong> Organized list of technical skills with icons for programming languages, frameworks, and tools, making it easy for visitors to assess my competencies at a glance.</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Page:</strong> Includes options to email me directly or connect on LinkedIn, making it easy for visitors to get in touch.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Tech Stack -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
        <p>This portfolio was developed using the following technologies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Blazor:</strong> Core framework for building interactive web pages using C# instead of JavaScript.</li>
            <li><strong>ASP.NET Core:</strong> Backend framework providing the foundation for the Blazor application, allowing seamless component-based development.</li>
            <li><strong>Bootstrap:</strong> CSS framework for styling, creating responsive, mobile-first web layouts.</li>
            <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Code repository for version control and sharing the project with the community.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Challenges Faced -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Challenges Faced</h2>
        <p>Creating a single-page application with Blazor posed several challenges, including managing state between components and optimizing load times for the client side. Additionally, designing an intuitive navigation system and making the site responsive across various devices required careful layout planning and styling adjustments.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Outcomes -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Key Outcomes</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Successfully deployed a fully responsive, single-page portfolio website with interactive components.</li>
            <li>Improved understanding of component-based development and the Blazor framework.</li>
            <li>Enhanced skills in creating responsive layouts with Bootstrap, making the site accessible and visually appealing across devices.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Links -->
    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Links</h2>
        <p>Check out the project source code on GitHub!</p>
        <a href="https://github.com/your-repo-link" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-primary me-2">GitHub Repository</a>
        <a href="https://your-live-demo-link.com" target="_blank" class="btn btn-outline-success">Live Demo</a>
    </section>
</div>